---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
import Header from "../components/Header.astro";
import Footer from "../components/Footer.astro";
---
<BaseLayout title="Shop • Historical Translation Project™">
  <Header />
  <main class="mx-auto max-w-6xl px-4 py-14">
    <div class="max-w-3xl">
      <div class="kicker">Shop</div>
      <h1 class="mt-3 h-serif text-4xl sm:text-5xl">Shopify-ready commerce architecture</h1>
      <p class="mt-6 text-ink-900/70 leading-relaxed text-lg">
        Even if you use a fulfillment center, Shopify can still handle checkout, payment processing, taxes, and order capture—
        then transmit shipping/line-item details to your fulfillment partner via native integrations or apps.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="mt-12 grid gap-6 md:grid-cols-2">
      <div class="card p-8">
        <div class="h-serif text-2xl">What Shopify provides</div>
        <ul class="mt-4 space-y-2 text-ink-900/70">
          <li>• Secure payments + checkout</li>
          <li>• Product catalog + pricing</li>
          <li>• Customer emails + order confirmations</li>
          <li>• Discounts, subscriptions, and tax settings</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
      <div class="card p-8">
        <div class="h-serif text-2xl">Fulfillment flow</div>
        <ul class="mt-4 space-y-2 text-ink-900/70">
          <li>• Customer places order on Shopify</li>
          <li>• Order is routed to fulfillment center (API/app)</li>
          <li>• Fulfillment center ships and returns tracking</li>
          <li>• Shopify notifies customer and records status</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="mt-10 card p-8">
      <div class="kicker">Status</div>
      <div class="mt-2 h-serif text-2xl">Storefront coming soon</div>
      <p class="mt-3 text-ink-900/70">
        This site is structured so purchase buttons can point to Shopify product pages as soon as your catalog is live.
      </p>
    </div>
  </main>
  <Footer />
</BaseLayout>
